         <div type="translation" resp="#cmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><note>i</note>: In this tomb lies the body of [ -]rus, of good memory. He lived more or less 30 years. He left this world in the year 6 thousand 477, day 15 in the month August.</p>
            <p><note>ii</note>: Oh all you who pass on the road, behold and [see] if your grief is such as my grief. Pray for me that thus I may have God as my helper in the day of judgement. Amen.</p>
            
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>ii.1: See Lamentations 1.12, available at <ref target="http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0527.tlg051.perseus-lat1:1.12">Perseus</ref>.</p>
